grave;nh vn c nhng ngi d&acirc;n thng xuy&ecirc;n ti lui ti b&agrave;y t l&ograve;ng th&agrave;nh k&iacute;nh. C c gi&aacute;o theo ch&acirc;n nhng ngi ch&acirc;u &Acirc;u v&agrave;o Vit Nam, gi&uacute;p H&agrave; Ni c&oacute; c Nh&agrave; th Ln, Nh&agrave; th Ca Bc, Nh&agrave; th H&agrave;m Long</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c807626d2f_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Ch&ugrave;a Mt Ct, mt c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh c hin nm trong khu ph Ph&aacute;p</em></p>\r\n<h2>m thc</h2>\r\n<p>L&agrave; trung t&acirc;m vn h&oacute;a ca c min Bc t nhiu th k, ti H&agrave; Ni c&oacute; th t&igrave;m thy v&agrave; thng thc nhng m&oacute;n n ca nhiu v&ugrave;ng t kh&aacute;c, nhng m thc th&agrave;nh ph cng n&oacute; nhng n&eacute;t ri&ecirc;ng bit. Cm l&agrave;ng V&ograve;ng c nhng ngi d&acirc;n ca ng&ocirc;i l&agrave;ng c&ugrave;ng t&ecirc;n thuc qun Cu Giy l&agrave;m c trng bi m&ugrave;i thm v&agrave; m&agrave;u sc. Cm l&agrave;m t ging np v&agrave;ng gt khi c&ograve;n non, g&oacute;i trong nhng t&agrave;u l&aacute; sen m&agrave;u ngc thch v&agrave; c nhng ngi b&aacute;n h&agrave;ng rao b&aacute;n ngay t s&aacute;ng sm. Tuy ph bin nht l&agrave; cm ti, nhng m&oacute;n n n&agrave;y c&ograve;n c ch bin th&agrave;nh m&oacute;n ch cm. &acirc;y cng l&agrave; mt m&oacute;n qu&agrave; c d&ugrave;ng trong c&aacute;c dp vui</p>\r\n<p>Thanh Tr&igrave;, mt v&ugrave;ng ngoi &ocirc; kh&aacute;c, ni ting vi m&oacute;n b&aacute;nh cun. B&aacute;nh c l&agrave;m t go gi&eacute; c&aacute;nh, t&aacute;m thm, tr&aacute;ng mng nh t giy. Nhng ph n v&ugrave;ng Thanh Tr&igrave; cho b&aacute;nh v&agrave;o th&uacute;ng, i tr&ecirc;n u v&agrave; i rao khp c&aacute;c ng&otilde; ph ca H&agrave; Ni. B&aacute;nh xp trong th&uacute;ng, tng lp gi nhau tr&ecirc;n nhng t&agrave;u l&aacute; chui. Khi n, b&aacute;nh c b&oacute;c tng lp ri cun li, b&agrave;y tr&ecirc;n nhng chic a. M&oacute;n b&aacute;nh cun Thanh Tr&igrave; c n c&ugrave;ng vi loi nc mm pha theo c&ocirc;ng thc c bit ca ngi Thanh Tr&igrave;, u ph r&aacute;n n&oacute;ng, ch qu. Ng&agrave;y nay, b&aacute;nh c&ograve;n c n vi tht ba ch quay gi&ograve;n</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c80781db03_crop.JPG" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Mt b&aacute;t ph b&ograve; ch&iacute;n n c&ugrave;ng vi quy.</em></p>\r\n<p>Mt m&oacute;n n kh&aacute;c ca H&agrave; Ni, tuy xut hin cha l&acirc;u nhng &atilde; ni ting, l&agrave; ch c&aacute; L&atilde; Vng. V&agrave;o thi Ph&aacute;p thuc, gia &igrave;nh h o&agrave;n ph H&agrave;ng Sn, ng&agrave;y nay l&agrave; ph Ch C&aacute;, &atilde; to n&ecirc;n mt m&oacute;n n m&agrave; danh ting ca n&oacute; l&agrave;m thay i c t&ecirc;n con ph. Ch c l&agrave;m t tht c&aacute; lng &ndash; hoc c&aacute; qu, c&aacute; nheo nhng s k&eacute;m ngon hn &ndash; th&aacute;i mng p vi nc ring, ngh, m, ht ti&ecirc;u, nc mm ri kp v&agrave;o cp tre nng tr&ecirc;n l&ograve; than ngay tr&ecirc;n b&agrave;n n ca thc kh&aacute;ch. Ch c&aacute; L&atilde; Vng phi n n&oacute;ng, k&egrave;m vi b&aacute;nh a nng hay b&uacute;n ri, lc rang, rau m&ugrave;i, h&uacute;ng l&aacute;ng, th&igrave; l&agrave;, h&agrave;nh c ti ch nh, chm vi mm t&ocirc;m.</p>\r\n<p>Ph l&agrave; m&oacute;n n rt ph bin  Vit Nam, nhng ph H&agrave; Ni c&oacute; nhng c&aacute;ch ch bin c trng ri&ecirc;ng. Ph H&agrave; Ni mang v ngt ca xng b&ograve;, tht va ch&iacute;n n   vn do m&agrave; kh&ocirc;ng dai, m&agrave;u nc ph trong, b&aacute;nh ph mng v&agrave; mm. Sau khi c trn qua nc n&oacute;ng, b&aacute;nh ph c d&agrave;n u trong b&aacute;t, b&ecirc;n tr&ecirc;n l&agrave; nhng l&aacute;t tht mng c&ugrave;ng h&agrave;nh hoa, rau thm. C&ugrave;ng vi thi gian, nhiu m&oacute;n ph mi xut hin vi nhng c&aacute;ch ch bin kh&aacute;c nhau, nh ph x&agrave;o, ph r&aacute;n...</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', '11:27:23', 1, 'admin');
INSERT INTO news_article_revision (revision_id, article_id, category_id, title, sub_title, slug, description, content, author, icons, created_date, created_user_id, created_user_name) VALUES (4, 3, 4, 'Hoan Kiem Lake', '', 'hoan-kiem-lake', '<p><strong>Hoan Kiem Lake</strong> (Vietnamese: H Ho&agrave;n Kim, meaning "Lake of the Returned Sword" or "Lake of the Restored Sword", also known as H Gm - Sword Lake) is a lake in the historical center of Hanoi, the capital city of Vietnam. The lake is one of the major scenic spots in the city and serves as a focal point for its public life.</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">&lt;h2&gt;History&lt;/h2&gt;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&lt;p&gt;According to the legend, emperor L&ecirc; Li handed a magic sword called Heaven''s Will which brought him victory in his revolt against the Chinese Ming Dynasty back to the Golden Turtle God (Kim Qui) in the lake and hence gave it its present name (the lake was formerly known as "Luc Thuy" meaning "Green Water"). The Tortoise Tower (Thap R&ugrave;a) standing on a small island near the center of lake is linked to the legend.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c880db619c_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Turtle Tower</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Large soft-shell turtles, either of the species Rafetus swinhoei or a separate species named Rafetus leloii in honor of the emperor, have been sighted in the lake. The species is critically endangered and the number of individuals in the lake is unclear.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://phuocnh/tomatocms/upload/news/admin/2010/08/4c7c880ed46f3_crop.jpg" alt="" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>The Huc Bridge</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />Near the northern shore of the lake lies Jade Island on which the Ngoc Son Temple (Jade Mountain Temple) stands. The temple was erected in the 18th century. It honors the 13-century military leader Tran Hung Dao who distinguished himself in the fight against the Yuan Dynasty, Van Xuong, a scholar, and Nguyen Van Sieu, a Confucian master and famous writer in charge of repairs made to the temple in 1864. Jade Island is connected to the shore by the wooden red-painted Huc Bridge (The Huc, meaning Morning Sunlight Bridge).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&lt;/p&gt;</p>', 'Wikipedia', '', '11:44:51', 1, 'admin');
